name: SUNRISES
description: The following four works are part of a mini series with the main sequence. (Art within Art within Art has a certain Inception-like quality to it.) There's 4 parts to a day, right? (Wait, what?) Sunrise/Sunset/Moonrise/Moonset. (but ummm during a new moon there is no moonrise or moonset)...doesn't mean the moon isn't there. So, for these four works, we have 3 gradient circles that have been somewhat blended together with three words directly underneath; all begin with either SUN or MOON. First we see the light, then the sun rises, and then it ascends. We have successfully completed the first movement.
